<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-18T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-18T21:00:00-05:00" n="489" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24591/3: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-18T22:00:00-04:00">March 18,
                                    1943—10 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>132. Your 23, January 8 and 20, February 23. The Department is sending by
                            airmail a draft agreement<note n="37" xml:id="d489fn37">
                                <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_459">p.
                                459</ref>.</note> relating to the entry into and presence in Iran of
                            armed forces and other agencies of the United States of America,
                            together with the President’s full power authorizing you to negotiate,
                            conclude and sign such an agreement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>